ADDITIONAL TERMS — ETHICAL USE CLAUSE

While the MIT License grants broad permissions, the author respectfully requests
that all users of ReconRadar adhere to the following ethical guidelines:

1. AUTHORIZED USE ONLY
   ReconRadar must only be used against systems, networks, and domains for which
   you have explicit, written authorization from the rightful owner. Unauthorized
   use against third-party systems may violate the Computer Fraud and Abuse Act
   (CFAA), the Computer Misuse Act (CMA), GDPR, and equivalent laws in your
   jurisdiction.

2. NO MALICIOUS USE
   This software must not be used for unauthorized data collection, surveillance,
   stalking, competitive intelligence against organizations without consent,
   cyberattacks, or any activity that could cause harm to individuals or
   organizations.

3. RESPONSIBLE DISCLOSURE
   If you discover vulnerabilities using this tool during an authorized engagement,
   you are encouraged to follow responsible disclosure practices and notify the
   affected organization before publishing any findings.

4. BUG BOUNTY & PENETRATION TESTING
   Use of ReconRadar within the defined scope of a bug bounty program (HackerOne,
   Bugcrowd, Intigriti, etc.) or a signed penetration testing engagement is
   explicitly permitted and encouraged.

5. NO WARRANTY FOR ILLEGAL USE
   The author assumes NO LIABILITY for any damages, legal consequences, or
   harm arising from misuse of this software. By using ReconRadar, you agree
   that you are solely responsible for ensuring your use is lawful and authorized.

